         I'd like to point out one important thing that you people seem to be forgetting... THIS IS A GAME. It's not the real world, bound by rules of physics and reality, it's thousands of lines of code. What everyone is saying about being able to stack regen\debuffs etc just because they're all duration based spells is flawed. You could have easily said a few months ago that you can't have an item that increases your nuke damage, or makes your spells cast faster. You need to remember that it's all CODE, and they could easily program a much more intricate system with the spells, allowing ONLY DoTs to stack. Just because it's not currently implemented or feasable, doesn't mean it can't be.</P><P>You need to, "think outside the box". <img src=icon_smile_big.gif border=0 align=middle></P><P>~ Xarslik Malarslik ~</P><P>57th Scaled Defiler of the 7th Hammer<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
